    "For the purpose of this exercise, we will are going to use [grid.168010.e](https://grid.ac/institutes/grid.168010.e). Feel free though to change the parameters below as you want, eg by [choosing another GRID organization](https://grid.ac/institutes).\n"

   ],
   "source": [
    "GRIDID = \"grid.168010.e\" #@param {type:\"string\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "#\n",
    "# gen link to Dimensions\n",
    "#\n",
    "def dimensions_url(grids):\n",
    "    root = \"https://app.dimensions.ai/discover/publication?or_facet_research_org=\"\n",
    "    return root + \"&or_facet_research_org=\".join([x for x in grids])\n",
    "\n",
    "from IPython.core.display import display, HTML\n",
    "display(HTML('---<br /><a href=\"{}\">Preview {} Dimensions &#x29c9;</a>'.format(dimensions_url([GRIDID]), GRIDID)))"
   ]

    "## Publications most cited : which research areas?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "Collapsed": "false",
    "colab": {},
    "colab_type": "code",
    "id": "FzJ-rQwpI-Aj",
    "outputId": "ab50770a-e619-433d-9948-24ca5d8dc422"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Returned Publications: 1000 (total = 235309)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "data = dslquery(f\"\"\"search publications \n",
    "                    where research_orgs.id=\"{GRIDID}\" \n",
    "                    return publications[doi+title+times_cited+category_for+journal] \n",
    "                    sort by times_cited limit 1000\"\"\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "Collapsed": "false",
    "colab_type": "text",
    "id": "nBaQaA0MI-Aj"
   },
   "source": [
    "Most publications have one or more associated Field Of Research (FOR) category, which is represented in the JSON like this:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "{'category_for' : [{'id': '3292', 'name': '1402 Applied Economics'}, \n",
    "                    {'id': '3177', 'name': '1117 Public Health and Health Services'}]\n",
    "                    }`\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "However since some publications may not have an associated FOR category, the resulting JSON in some cases may not have `category_for` as a key. Since we want to import the data into pandas we need to ensure the key is always there and has an empty list when no category is available.  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "Collapsed": "false"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# dimcli.shortcuts.normalize_key takes: field name / json list / value to add when the field is not found\n",
    "normalize_key(\"category_for\", data.publications, [])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {
    "Collapsed": "false",
    "colab": {},

    "                    where research_orgs.id=\"{GRIDID}\" \n",

   "source": [
    "fundersdata = dsl.query(f\"\"\"search grants \n",
    "                        where research_orgs.id=\"{GRIDID}\" \n",
    "                        return funders aggregate funding \n",
    "                        sort by funding\"\"\")\n",
    "df = fundersdata.as_dataframe()\n",
    "df.head(10)"
   ]
